<task id="001" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D1-01 Provision `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search Index</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 1 — Platform Extensions</phase>
    <wave>P1-G1 (serial; foundation; blocks 002, 003, 007)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <tags>infrastructure, ai-search, bff, bicep, rag</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Provision the new `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search index on Spaarke Dev. The
    index hosts session-scoped chunked file content for the R5 chat-driven "Summarize a
    Document" vertical slice. Schema mirrors the existing canonical
    `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` (3072-dim HNSW + BM25 + semantic config) and adds a
    `sessionId` field so the cleanup `IHostedService` (task 007) and the RAG search path
    (task 002) can scope queries to an individual chat session. Per ADR-014, every
    document MUST carry both `tenantId` AND `sessionId`. The Bicep module that provisions
    the index MUST be idempotent — re-running on an existing environment is a no-op.

    R5 is configuration-first: this task ships infrastructure-as-code and an index JSON
    schema. It does NOT modify BFF code, so the BFF publish-size budget is not consumed
    by this task. It DOES unblock the entire downstream P1-G2/G3/G4/G5 wave.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior infrastructure engineer with Azure AI Search + Bicep experience. Deep
    familiarity with HNSW vector field configuration, semantic ranker setup, and
    idempotent Bicep deployments against Spaarke Dev.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search index is provisioned on Spaarke Dev with
    a schema that mirrors `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` (3072-dim HNSW vector field with
    `text-embedding-3-large`, BM25 keyword retrieval, semantic configuration) and adds
    `sessionId` (filterable, facetable) alongside the existing `tenantId` field. The
    Bicep module that creates the index is committed to the repo and is idempotent
    (`az deployment` re-runs succeed without error). A test query
    `POST /indexes/spaarke-session-files/docs/search` against the empty index returns an
    empty hit set with no auth errors. Acceptance criteria below are all green.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-design">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-index">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-index-schema">infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-knowledge-index-v2.json</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">All `spaarke-session-files` index documents MUST carry both `tenantId` AND `sessionId` for tenant isolation + session scoping. Both fields MUST be filterable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — this task adds infrastructure-as-code only; verify no BFF binary impact. Index provisioning does NOT consume R5's ≤+1 MB BFF publish-size budget.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — N/A for this task (no service registrations). Confirm.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-03">Multi-tenancy — initial scope is shared index with `tenantId` + `sessionId` filters. Per-tenant dedicated session-files indexes are deferred to a Phase 1 spike (see spec.md Open Decisions § "Per-tenant routing for session-files index"). Document the routing decision in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07">BFF publish-size — index provisioning is not BFF code; no `dotnet publish` measurement required for this task. Confirm publish-size delta = 0 MB in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md MUST">MUST emit `tenantId` + `sessionId` on every `spaarke-session-files` index document per ADR-014 — encode as required filterable fields.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 reuse mandate (CLAUDE.md §3.1)">MUST copy schema shape from `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` (3072-dim HNSW + BM25 + semantic config) — do NOT invent a parallel schema. Add only the `sessionId` field beyond the canonical reference.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Bicep module MUST be idempotent — re-running the deployment on an environment that already has the index MUST NOT fail and MUST NOT data-destructively re-create the index.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Embedding model selection — `text-embedding-3-large` (3072 dims) per spec.md Open Decisions to match knowledge-index parity. May revisit in Phase 1 spike if cost telemetry surfaces issues.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>azure-ai-search/index-provisioning</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/rag-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/auth-AI-azure-resources.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching-tenant-isolation.md</file>
      <file>infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-knowledge-index-v2.json</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Index schema canonical reference" location="infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-knowledge-index-v2.json">
        Copy this file's structure as the starting point. Add `sessionId` field
        (Edm.String, filterable=true, facetable=true, searchable=false, sortable=false)
        adjacent to the existing `tenantId` field. Preserve all other fields, the
        3072-dim HNSW vector field configuration, scoring profiles, and the semantic
        configuration unchanged. Change the `"name"` to `"spaarke-session-files"`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Bicep idempotency for AI Search indexes" location="infrastructure/ (existing modules)">
        Search for the existing Bicep module that provisions `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2`
        and either extend it to also provision `spaarke-session-files` (parameterize)
        OR add a sibling module following the same shape. Use `az search` REST API via
        deployment script resource if direct Bicep resource is not available for index
        schema; ensure conditional-create semantics so re-runs are no-ops.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice. Users upload up to 20
      files per chat session; those files are chunked, embedded, and indexed into a
      dedicated `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search index. The index is queried by
      the existing `RagService` (extended in task 002 with a `sessionId` filter) and
      swept by a new background `IHostedService` (task 007) when sessions end. Choosing
      a dedicated index (vs. extending `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` with a `sessionId`
      filter) was an explicit decision per design.md §4.2 / spec.md Open Decisions: it
      provides clean isolation, simple eviction, and doesn't pollute customer-corpus
      query metrics with ephemeral session traffic.
    </background>
    <dependencies></dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>`spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` provisioning — canonical reference and the
        existing index this schema mirrors. Located in `infrastructure/ai-search/`.</item>
      <item>Task 002 (D1-02) extends `RagSearchOptions` with a `sessionId` filter and
        routes `RagService.SearchAsync()` to this new index. Task 003 (D1-03)
        parameterizes `RagIndexingPipeline` to write to this index. Task 007 (D1-07)
        sweeps documents from this index on session-end. All three depend on task 001.</item>
      <item>R2 Insights Engine added scope shape migration to the knowledge index
        (`scripts/Migrate-InsightsIndexScopeShape.ps1`) — referenced as a similar
        provisioning pattern; not a direct dependency.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`.
      Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL per CLAUDE.md §8 (infrastructure change + downstream
      blocker for 8+ tasks).
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm task 001 status is 🔲, dependencies are
      empty, parallel-safe = false. Read `current-task.md` to verify no prior R5 task is
      in flight. Read project README for project status.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract
      from `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2.json`: full field list, HNSW vector configuration
      (3072 dims, algorithm parameters), scoring profiles, semantic configuration. Read
      ADR-014 in full and confirm the tenant-isolation contract.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Locate Existing Bicep Provisioning">
      Search `infrastructure/` for the existing Bicep module(s) that provision Azure AI
      Search indexes. Identify the pattern used (direct Bicep resource vs deployment
      script vs ARM template). Confirm how `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` is currently
      created on Spaarke Dev. Decide between extending the existing module vs. adding a
      sibling module. Document the decision in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author Index Schema JSON">
      Create `infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-session-files.json` by copying
      `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2.json` verbatim, then: (a) change `"name"` to
      `"spaarke-session-files"`; (b) add the `sessionId` field (Edm.String, filterable,
      facetable, non-searchable, non-sortable) adjacent to `tenantId`; (c) preserve
      every other field, HNSW configuration, scoring profile, and semantic configuration
      unchanged. Diff against canonical to verify only intended deltas.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Extend Bicep Module(s)">
      Extend or add the Bicep module to provision the new index. Ensure idempotency:
      re-runs must succeed without error and must not destroy existing data. Parameterize
      the index name + schema-file path where the existing module pattern supports it.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Deploy to Spaarke Dev">
      Run the deployment against Spaarke Dev via `az deployment ...` (using the
      `azure-deploy` skill if applicable). Verify the index appears in Azure Portal.
      Capture the deployment output + Portal screenshot reference for task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Smoke Test the Empty Index">
      Issue a `POST /indexes/spaarke-session-files/docs/search` against the empty index
      using `az rest` or `curl` with the Azure Search admin key (via Key Vault per
      ADR-028 pattern). Confirm: (a) auth succeeds; (b) response is an empty `value: []`
      hit set; (c) no schema-validation errors. Capture the response for task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Idempotency">
      Re-run the Bicep deployment a second time. Confirm: deployment succeeds, index
      schema is unchanged, no data destruction. Capture the second deployment output.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and confirm each is testable +
      passing. Record evidence per criterion in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new files (index JSON + Bicep). Run `adr-check`
      skill against the new files; verify ADR-014 (tenant isolation), ADR-029 (BFF
      publish hygiene — N/A but confirmed), ADR-010 (DI minimalism — N/A but confirmed).
      Both gates MUST pass before marking the task complete.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 001 🔲 → ✅. Reset
      `current-task.md` to the next pending task per CLAUDE.md §7. Record the per-tenant
      routing decision (initial shared index with `tenantId` + `sessionId` filters; spike
      deferred) in task notes. Note BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code changed).
      Report task completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="az">Azure CLI — Bicep deployment, AI Search index REST calls, Key Vault secret retrieval</tool>
    <tool name="pac">Power Platform CLI — not directly used by this task; available if downstream Dataverse coordination surfaces</tool>
    <tool name="dotnet">Not used directly (no BFF code change) — available for verification builds if requested</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit the new index JSON + Bicep changes on the R5 branch</tool>
    <tool name="azure-deploy">Skill for executing Bicep deployments per Spaarke conventions</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="infrastructure">infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-session-files.json (NEW)</output>
    <output type="infrastructure">infrastructure/ (Bicep module extension — extends existing AI Search provisioning to include `spaarke-session-files`)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status: 001 🔲 → ✅)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/current-task.md (reset to next task)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/task-001-deployment-evidence.md (deployment output, Portal screenshot reference, smoke-test response, idempotency-run evidence, per-tenant routing decision)</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report (per task-execute template Step 6)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Index `spaarke-session-files` is visible in the Azure Portal AI Search resource on Spaarke Dev.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Index schema field set matches `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` plus the mandatory `tenantId` AND `sessionId` fields (both Edm.String, filterable=true, facetable=true).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">HNSW vector field is configured at 3072 dimensions matching the `text-embedding-3-large` embedding model.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BM25 keyword retrieval AND a semantic configuration are present, mirroring `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Bicep module is idempotent — a second `az deployment` run against the same environment succeeds without error and does not destroy or recreate the existing index.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke test `POST /indexes/spaarke-session-files/docs/search` against the empty index returns an empty hit set (`value: []`) with no auth errors and no schema-validation errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Task notes record the per-tenant routing decision (initial shared index with `tenantId` + `sessionId` filters; per-tenant dedicated indexes deferred to a Phase 1 spike per spec.md Open Decisions).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (confirmed in task notes; no BFF code changed by this task).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
